Everything is sorta all fixed now, last problem of getting the wifi extend to the whole house but that's pretty small in comparison to the past madness I've been dealing with. Yeah, that's my 2018. Hahaha how's yours?

Call pg&e and then they said they would get it back together by the end of the night, pretty hilarious at this point. Like what else could go wrong. So we have dinner In the dark. No electricity means no wifi so my family and I were literally just sitting around lol Then a little grandma gets dropped off in front of our place and she starts fighting with the passenger seat, typical Asian fight "let me pay you back" "no I don't want your money" " not let me pay you" etc etc and my whole family lines up against our front window and watches..... because we are nosey and bored lolololol

So once we think the water heater madness was over, pg&e send out a notification that they are doing maintenance and we will not have power during the day. Sounded fine but a part of me knew that with our luck something bad was bound to happen. Sooo of course it did. They finished early and at first we were like omg we got out free... nawwwww few hours later black out. Greatttt.

They person on the phone had the balls to tell me that they had no technician to which the plumber who was still standing with us in front of the water heater laugh and he whispers, that's not possible, tell them you'll sue. So again with the white people voice I threaten to sue and demand to speak with a manager. When I get the manager on the phone, all of a sudden they have technicians now but they can only send parts on Monday.... like no hot water for over a week then!?! So basically we had to go to friends houses and stuff to shower for a week while we waited for parts and the technician. Such fun. Lolol

Okay, so I'm not crazy, there was gas and at this point I'd like like to throw in an "I told you soâ. He tells us to call the company since we are under warranty. As I'm calling the next guy comes, now the water heater doesn't even turn on. And the company tells me that they can send parts but they aren't paying for labor. Like what? You give me a faulty water boiler and you want me to pay to fix it? Heck naw, so I was like you need to send me a technician to diagnose the issue and fix the problem because gas is leaking into my house and I don't know when the water heater is gonna explode and kill me, etc etc in my best white people voice

So we call another company. We end up finding two to come look at our water heater. First guy turns it on. Says oh looks fine. Now I'm thinking oh gosh, we coulda had hot water the past two days but we didn't turn it on? Gahhhh. But then, after like 5 or so minutes of talking with him, we smell the gas again and as soon as we process that the gas is leaking again the water boiler shoots out fire and makes this huge explosive noises like bang fire bang fire. And we all jump back

They make an appointment with us the next day... they said we'll be there at 10am, never showed up, called them at 11 and they said there's delays and that they'd be there soon... soon never comes basically they kept saying soon, we call after soon and they say later and then later passes and we call again, it was madness. They could have just said we won't get to you today be then we wouldn't have been waiting at home for them but no they kept saying soon from like 10am until 8:30pm. Like gah dang. And then we call back h to next day and we're like yesterday was ridiculous and not okay, you promised to be here by 10, then by 4, then by 7, then by 8:30 and all those times no one showed up and we still have no hot water, and the guy with spectacular costumer service said "if you are that unhappy with us you, there are plenty of other companies, you can use someone else..... we are a big corporation" blah blah blah, like no your service sucks butt and you are a butthole.

The pg&e guy says he doesn't smell it either and that it's a simple fix. I mean idk but gas was leaking and apparently my mom had seen fire from the burner spew out of the contained tank.... doesn't sound safe or easy... thanks firefighters and pg&e. At this point we started to think we were the crazy ones like hmm maybe there wasn't any gas smell, but at the same time I was like, no I'm so certain it was gas. So we called another Asian contractor to fix it and basically since he only kinda knows what he's doing, he says that we should have someone else take a look at it, sighhhh.. So we had no hot water that day. We call to schedule the repair person whose number is on the water heater...
